				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I have 16 objects, and I have a small table of numbers relatively-prime to 16. Each frame I cycle through the objects adding a relatively-prime number to choose the next object index, and call each object's draw routine in that order (the draw routines just fill up the OAM buffer in linear order as tiles are added). Every frame I just advance to the next number in the table. I always start the index at 0, allowing me to use sprite-0 hit if necessary and to always prioritize one of the objects.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

