						<div class="postbody">An RNG seems like a bad idea. It tends to be 50% whatever on average but since it's not uniform that means there can be runs of one or the other state, thus uneven flickering. Audibly it's like the difference between a low tone and a geiger counter clicking rapidly.</div>

